In the first part of the course the literary situation existed before disintegration of the USSR, and the forms of literature life (official literature, 
"samizdat", "tamizdat" ) is considered. The special attention is given to the epoch of Gorbachev's reforms and to transformations of a literary 
life during the subsequent period. The general review of a modern situation is given. The modern Russian prose and poetry are analyzed at the 
seminars, and students receive the general notion on features of the modern literature.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The purpose of the course is to give notion about the modern trends in  Russian literature. The first part of the course is devoted to the 
description of the Soviet literature as unique governmental/ideological device. Then transformation of this system in 90th of XX century is 
considered and selected works of modern Russian prose writers and poets are analyzed.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course the student   1) knows the peculiarities  of the Russian literature of the Soviet period 2) is familiar with modern Russian literary life (publishing houses, magazines, prizes) 3) can analyse works of modern Russian authors 4) knows works of the basic Russian literary critics 5) is capable to prove own estimation of the modern literary text
